    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A French variation of Art Nouveau, particularly used to describe artistic trends in various discplines such as architecture, the applied arts, and decorative arts around the turn of the 20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een Franse variant van art nouveau. De term wordt met name gebruikt om artistieke trends te beschrijven in diverse disciplines als architectuur, toegepaste kunsten en kunstnijverheid rond het begin van de 20ste eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>法國的新藝術運動，特別用以描述各種不同學門的藝術風潮，例如二十世紀初左右的建築、應用美術和裝飾藝術。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
